{
  "_about": "Concordance test set for Reviewer2. Unlike ErrorCatch (which measures whether the second-reviewer FLAGS disagreements), this measures ACCURACY: does the deterministic engine's INDEPENDENT classification match an external expert standard? 'expert_truth' is the expert-panel / ClinGen-VCEP (3-star) ClinVar germline classification — chosen as an INDEPENDENT gold standard NOT derived from this engine. The engine never reads 'expert_truth'; it only sees the population/computational/assertion evidence. Crucially this set INCLUDES cases the v1 engine is EXPECTED to miss (e.g. pathogenic-by-functional-assay, where PS3 is not implemented) so the concordance number is honest, not inflated. This is a HAND-CURATED ILLUSTRATIVE set with real gene/accession context; a production run needs the live ClinVar/gnomAD/VEP provider (v1.1). n is reported so the metric stays honest.",
